# Real app routes fall back to the SPA shell (200) so React Router can render
# them client-side — this matters for paths not covered by prerendering yet
# (e.g. a brand-new Sanity post, or /donate/success after a live Stripe
# redirect). Listed explicitly rather than a blanket /* so that genuinely
# unknown paths fall through to Cloudflare's automatic 404.html handling
# below instead of silently returning 200 for a page that doesn't exist.
#
# Destination is "/" rather than "/index.html" — Cloudflare Pages auto-
# normalizes any request/rewrite touching a literal "/index.html" or
# "*.html" path, and when the source pattern also ends in "/" or "/*" that
# normalization loops back into this same rule, which Cloudflare's linter
# detects and silently disables the whole rule (see deploy log: "Infinite
# loop detected... has been ignored"). "/" resolves to the exact same file
# (this is a static SPA shell either way) without tripping that check.
